{"pageProps":{"eyebrow":"eunomia-bpf","page":{"layout":"document","title":"ecc docker usage","description":"``shell yourprogram.bpf.c yourprogram.h optional, if you want to use ring buffer to export events ``","bodyHtml":"<h2 id=\"docker-usage\">docker usage</h2>\n<p>The only file you will need to write is:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">your_program.bpf.c</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">your_program.h</span><span style=\"color:#768390\">  # optional, if you want to use ring buffer to export events</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>after that, simply run this:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> docker</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -it</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -v</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> /path/to/repo/:/src</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ghcr.io/eunomia-bpf/ecc-`</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">uname</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -m</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">`</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">:latest</span><span style=\"color:#768390\"> # use absolute path</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>you will get a <code>package.json</code> in your root dir. Just run:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./ecli</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> package.json</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>to start it you can download <code>ecli</code> tool from <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/releases\">eunomia-bpf/releases</a>, we have pre-build binaries for linux x86. Small and No dependencies, besides glibc and glibcxx. Or just run this:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> wget</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> https://aka.pw/bpf-ecli</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -O</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ecli</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> &#x26;&#x26; </span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">chmod</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> +x</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ecli</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>The eBPF compiled code can run on different kernel versions(CO-RE).\nsee: <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf\">github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf</a> for details.</p>\n<h2 id=\"container-image\">container image</h2>\n<p>simply run:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> docker</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -it</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -v</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> /path/to/repo:/src</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ghcr.io/eunomia-bpf/ecc-`</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">uname</span><span style=\"color:#6CB6FF\"> -m</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\">`</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>Or you can do that without a container, which is listed below:</p>\n<h2 id=\"github-actions\">Github actions</h2>\n<p>Use <a href=\"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-template\">eunomia-bpf/eunomia-template</a> as a GitHub template to compile online. The template's <code>publish.yml</code> workflow compiles <code>src/package.json</code> and publishes it as a GitHub release asset. Only three steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>use this repo as a github template: see <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/creating-and-managing-repositories/creating-a-repository-from-a-template\">creating-a-repository-from-a-template</a></li>\n<li>modify <code>src/template.bpf.c</code>, commit it and wait for the workflow to stop</li>\n<li>download the generated <code>package.json</code> from the latest release of your fork, then run:</li>\n</ol>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"bash\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F69D50\">$</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> sudo</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> ./ecli</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> run</span><span style=\"color:#96D0FF\"> package.json</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<h2 id=\"notifications\">Notifications</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>We use the same c ebpf code as libbpf, so most libbpf ebpf c code can run without any modification.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Supported ebpf program types: <code>kprobe</code>, <code>tracepoint</code>, <code>fentry</code>, we will add more types in the future.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>If you want to use ring buffer to export events, you need to add <code>your_program.h</code> to your repo, and\ndefine the export data type in it, the export data type should be a C <code>struct</code>, for example:</p>\n<figure data-rehype-pretty-code-figure=\"\"><pre tabindex=\"0\" data-language=\"c\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\"><code data-language=\"c\" data-theme=\"github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"display: grid;\"><span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">struct</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> process_event {</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> pid;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> ppid;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    unsigned</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> exit_code;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    unsigned</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> long</span><span style=\"color:#F47067\"> long</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> duration_ns;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    char</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> comm</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">[TASK_COMM_LEN];</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    char</span><span style=\"color:#F69D50\"> filename</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">[MAX_FILENAME_LEN];</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#F47067\">    int</span><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\"> exit_event;</span></span>\n<span data-line=\"\"><span style=\"color:#ADBAC7\">};</span></span></code></pre></figure>\n<p>The name and field types are not limited, but we will prefer use standard C types. If multiple struct\nexists in the header, we will use the first one. The feature is only enabled if we found a <code>BPF_MAP_TYPE_RINGBUF</code>\nmap exists in the ebpf program.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>","headings":[{"id":"docker-usage","text":"docker usage","depth":2},{"id":"container-image","text":"container image","depth":2},{"id":"github-actions","text":"Github actions","depth":2},{"id":"notifications","text":"Notifications","depth":2}],"sourcePath":"https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia.dev/tree/main/docs/eunomia-bpf/ecc/docker-usage.md","metadata":{"updatedAt":"2026-03-08T04:58:07.000Z","createdAt":"2023-08-10T12:54:12.000Z","authors":[{"name":"云微","email":"1067852565@qq.com"},{"name":"oluceps","email":"ospp@oluceps.uk"}]},"path":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/docker-usage/","alternates":{"en":"/eunomia-bpf/ecc/docker-usage/","zh":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/docker-usage/"},"continuation":{"index":{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","description":"![GitHub release (latest by date)](https://github.com/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/releases) ![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf) ![DeepSource](https://deepsource.io/gh/eunomia-bpf/eunomia-bpf/?ref=reposi","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/"},"previous":{"title":"benchmark","description":"Most of the time, bpf-loader work as a library to load eBPF program. It will not affect eBPF program after the program has been loaded and attached.","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/benchmark/"},"next":{"title":"github template","description":"eunomia-template：使用 GitHub Actions 编译 eBPF 程序，并将生成的 package.json 发布为 Release 资产。历史上的 ebpm-template 仓库现在会重定向到这里。","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/github-template/"}},"sidebar":[{"title":"导航","items":[{"title":"教程","href":"/zh/tutorials/"},{"title":"博客","href":"/zh/blog/"},{"title":"bpftime","href":"/zh/bpftime/"},{"title":"eBPF×AI/LLMs","href":"/zh/GPTtrace/"},{"title":"eunomia-bpf","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/"},{"title":"生态","href":"/zh/others/"},{"title":"旧博客","href":"/zh/blogs/"}]},{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","items":[{"title":"eunomia-bpf：简化并增强eBPF，支持CO-RE[^1]和WebAssembly[^2]","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/","depth":0},{"title":"Project architecture","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/architecture/","depth":1},{"title":"benchmark","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/benchmark/","depth":1},{"title":"ecc docker usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/docker-usage/","depth":2},{"title":"github template","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/github-template/","depth":2},{"title":"eunomia-cc","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/","depth":1},{"title":"ecc usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecc/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"ecli dockerfile usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/ecli-dockerfile-usage/","depth":2},{"title":"ecli","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/","depth":1},{"title":"ecli server","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/ecli/server/","depth":2},{"title":"exporter","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/","depth":1},{"title":"usage","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/exporter/usage/","depth":2},{"title":"introduction","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/introduction/","depth":1},{"title":"eunomia-bpf 用户手册: 让 eBPF 程序的开发和部署尽可能简单","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/manual/","depth":1},{"title":"在线体验网站","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/online/","depth":1},{"title":"quickstart","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/quickstart/","depth":1},{"title":"build on android aarch64","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/build-android-arm/","depth":2},{"title":"build from source","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/build/","depth":2},{"title":"Install ecli and ecc","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/setup/","depth":1},{"title":"supporting-external-BTF","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/supporting-external-BTF/","depth":1},{"title":"video","href":"/zh/eunomia-bpf/video/","depth":1}]}]}},"__N_SSG":true}